    <header>Introduction</header>
    <div class="intro">
      
      <p> I simulate populations of agents playing games for fitness and the population evolves under an evolutionary algorithm. The Racket code is on my Github page, further information is on the Gitlab page of this project. Here I would narrate you the how-to.</p>
      
      
      <p> First of all, a player is a distinct set of interest. </p>
      
      <p> Each player can choose a strategy and the outcome would be combined in a matrix with corresponding payoffs </p>
      
      <p>
	Here is the payoff matrix of a very popular game: the Prisoner's Dilemma.
      </p>
